As a result of the bachelor's seminar, an independent research project in English linguistics, English-language literature or culture is written, with the main focus on some narrow and topical issue. The course is meant to support the student throughout the writing process. Theoretical and methodological principles of writing a bachelor's thesis are addressed as well as the tradition of writing academic texts in English. The student learns some practical tips for maximising the efficiency of the writing process and for succeeding in defending the thesis. The seminars are mostly dedicated to analysing and providing feedback on various chapters of students' BA theses.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Independent study of a specific research topic from the field of linguistics, literature or culture together with the acquaitance with and the application of academic writing. Bachelor's seminar gives a student an opportunity  - to familiarise themselves with the research methods in the fields of linguistics, literature and culture that are applied in English-speaking communities; - deepen one's knowledge in the selected field of research; - develop the ability to formulate a relevant research question and independently collect and interpret information; - further develop one's practical skills in creating an academic text in English.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has successfully completed the course - is familiar with the major theoretical principles and practical tips for writing an academic research paper in English; - is able to find suitable sources for one's research project and determine their credibility; - in cooperation with the supervisor is able to formulate a research question, select a suitable methodology, conduct research as well as analyse and interpret the results; - is able to write a well-argued academic text following the principles of Anglo-American writing.
